## 📋 Instruction Set (42 Opcodes)

### 1️⃣ Load/Store Instructions (8 opcodes, 0x00-0x07)

| Opcode | Name | Stack Effect | Purpose |
|--------|------|--------------|---------|
| 0x00 | PUSH | `[...] → [value, ...]` | Push 8-byte value onto stack |
| 0x01 | POP | `[value, ...] → [...]` | Pop from stack |
| 0x02 | LOAD | `[...] → [local_var, ...]` | Load local variable |
| 0x03 | STORE | `[value, ...] → [...]` | Store to local variable |
| 0x04 | LOADG | `[...] → [global_var, ...]` | Load global variable |
| 0x05 | STOREG | `[value, ...] → [...]` | Store to global variable |
| 0x06 | DUP | `[value, ...] → [value, value, ...]` | Duplicate top value |
| 0x07 | SWAP | `[a, b, ...] → [b, a, ...]` | Swap top two values |

**Implementation**: Direct stack/memory operations with bounds checking

**Example**:
```
PUSH 10      # Push 10: stack=[10]
PUSH 20      # Push 20: stack=[10, 20]
LOAD 0       # Load local[0]: stack=[10, 20, local_value]
STORE 1      # Store to local[1]: stack=[10, 20]
```

---

### 2️⃣ Arithmetic Instructions (8 opcodes, 0x10-0x17)

| Opcode | Name | Stack Effect | Operation |
|--------|------|--------------|-----------|
| 0x10 | ADD | `[a, b, ...] → [a+b, ...]` | a + b |
| 0x11 | SUB | `[a, b, ...] → [a-b, ...]` | a - b |
| 0x12 | MUL | `[a, b, ...] → [a*b, ...]` | a * b |
| 0x13 | DIV | `[a, b, ...] → [a/b, ...]` | a / b (integer) |
| 0x14 | MOD | `[a, b, ...] → [a%b, ...]` | a % b |
| 0x15 | NEG | `[a, ...] → [-a, ...]` | Negate |
| 0x16 | ABS | `[a, ...] → [abs(a), ...]` | Absolute value |
| 0x17 | INCR | `[a, ...] → [a+1, ...]` | Increment |

**Implementation**: Wrapping arithmetic for overflow handling

**Example**:
```
PUSH 10
PUSH 3
MUL         # Result: 30
PUSH 5
ADD         # Result: 35
```

---

### 3️⃣ Logic Instructions (8 opcodes, 0x20-0x27)

| Opcode | Name | Stack Effect | Operation |
|--------|------|--------------|-----------|
| 0x20 | AND | `[a, b, ...] → [a & b, ...]` | Bitwise AND |
| 0x21 | OR | `[a, b, ...] → [a \| b, ...]` | Bitwise OR |
| 0x22 | NOT | `[a, ...] → [~a, ...]` | Bitwise NOT |
| 0x23 | XOR | `[a, b, ...] → [a ^ b, ...]` | Bitwise XOR |
| 0x24 | EQ | `[a, b, ...] → [1 if a==b else 0, ...]` | Equal |
| 0x25 | NEQ | `[a, b, ...] → [1 if a!=b else 0, ...]` | Not equal |
| 0x26 | LT | `[a, b, ...] → [1 if a<b else 0, ...]` | Less than |
| 0x27 | LTE | `[a, b, ...] → [1 if a<=b else 0, ...]` | Less than or equal |

**Implementation**: Comparison returns 1 (true) or 0 (false)

**Example**:
```
PUSH 10
PUSH 5
LT          # 10 < 5? → 0 (false)
PUSH 1
ADD         # 0 + 1 = 1
```

---

### 4️⃣ Control Flow Instructions (8 opcodes, 0x30-0x37)

| Opcode | Name | Stack Effect | Purpose |
|--------|------|--------------|---------|
| 0x30 | JMP | `[...] → [...]` | Unconditional jump (4-byte address) |
| 0x31 | JIF | `[cond, ...] → [...]` | Jump if false (cond==0) |
| 0x32 | JIT | `[cond, ...] → [...]` | Jump if true (cond!=0) |
| 0x33 | CALL | `[...] → [...]` | Function call (4-byte address) |
| 0x34 | RET | `[...] → [...]` | Function return |
| 0x35 | LOOP | `[counter, ...] → [counter-1, ...]` | Loop (decrement counter) |
| 0x36 | CMPJMP | `[a, b, ...] → [...]` | Compare and jump if equal |
| 0x37 | NOP | `[...] → [...]` | No operation (padding) |

**Implementation**: 4-byte big-endian address format for jumps

**Example**:
```
# If-else pattern:
PUSH 10
PUSH 5
LT              # 10 < 5? → 0 (false)
JIT else_label  # If true, jump to else
PUSH 100        # Then: value = 100
JMP end_label   # Jump to end
# else_label:
PUSH 200        # Else: value = 200
# end_label:
PRINT           # Output value
```

