### 5️⃣ Array/String Instructions (8 opcodes, 0x40-0x43, 0x50-0x53)

#### Array Operations (0x40-0x43)

| Opcode | Name | Stack Effect | Purpose |
|--------|------|--------------|---------|
| 0x40 | ARRALLOC | `[size, ...] → [address, ...]` | Allocate array |
| 0x41 | ARRGET | `[addr, index, ...] → [element, ...]` | Get array element |
| 0x42 | ARRSET | `[addr, index, value, ...] → [...]` | Set array element |
| 0x43 | ARRLEN | `[addr, ...] → [length, ...]` | Get array length |

#### String Operations (0x50-0x53)

| Opcode | Name | Stack Effect | Purpose |
|--------|------|--------------|---------|
| 0x50 | STRALLOC | `[length, ...] → [address, ...]` | Allocate string |
| 0x51 | STRGET | `[addr, index, ...] → [char, ...]` | Get character |
| 0x52 | STRSET | `[addr, index, char, ...] → [...]` | Set character |
| 0x53 | STRLEN | `[addr, ...] → [length, ...]` | Get string length |

**Implementation**: Metadata-first heap layout with bounds checking

**Example**:
```
# Create array [1, 2, 3]
PUSH 3
ARRALLOC           # address on stack
DUP
PUSH 1
PUSH 0
ARRSET             # array[0] = 1
DUP
PUSH 2
PUSH 1
ARRSET             # array[1] = 2
DUP
PUSH 3
PUSH 2
ARRSET             # array[2] = 3

# Access element
PUSH 1
ARRGET             # [2]
PRINT              # Output: 2
```

